## Inherited from parent spec

### Binding constraints (from `.spec-md` ## 0)

The following constraints are normative for EVERY part (A–J) of this specification. A directive in any later part that conflicts with one of these is void.

1. **Platform & language commitment.** The solution MUST target **.NET 10** and MUST be **F#-first** end to end: engine, orchestration, UI, and tooling are all F#. The domain model MUST be expressed as F# records and discriminated unions. C# projects are admitted ONLY where they already exist in the Berreman tree as cloned dependencies (`../MathNetNumerics/Numerics/Numerics.csproj`, cited at `C:/GitHub/Berreman/Berreman/Berreman.slnx:8`). No part MAY introduce a new C# project.

2. **Reuse before invention.** Every directive that touches an area already served by a Berreman primitive MUST name and call that primitive rather than re-implementing it, and MUST cite it as `<file>:<symbol>` or `<file>:<line>`. New modules, files, or abstractions are admitted ONLY when they trace to a named directive in this spec; a new artefact with no such trace MUST be dropped. The 4×4 solver (`Solvers.fs` `OpticalSystemSolver`), the field model (`Fields.fs` `EmFieldSystem`), the tensor model (`MaterialProperties.fs` `OpticalProperties`), and the units constants (`Constants.fs`) MUST NOT be forked, re-derived, or shadowed.

3. **Canonical-units rule.** All physical quantities MUST be stored internally in the single canonical SI base already used by the engine — **meters** for length/thickness, with `WaveLength` reduced to meters via its `.value` member (`Fields.fs:284`). Conversion to and from any human-facing unit (nm, µm/mkm, Å, mm, eV, cm⁻¹) MUST happen ONLY at the UI/IO boundary. No part MAY store a non-SI unit in the domain model, a project JSON payload, or a `.binz` pickle.

4. **JSON-canonical / `.binz`-derived rule.** The canonical, hand/LLM-editable project definition MUST be JSON, validated against a published JSON Schema on load. Zipped FsPickler (`.binz`, via `Softellect.Sys.Core.serialize`/`BinaryZippedFormat`, `Core.fs:257`) MUST be used ONLY for derived/bulk artefacts (sweeps, field maps, fit histories, caches) referenced as sidecars from the JSON; it MUST NOT carry the canonical project definition. No part MAY serialize the domain project model with FsPickler.

5. **FuncUI audit gate.** The Avalonia.FuncUI clone at `C:\GitHub\Avalonia.FuncUI.Clone\` MUST pass the mandatory audit (defined in §A.9) and be cleared of all flagged content BEFORE it is linked. No part MAY reference, link, or build against the clone until the audit passes. The clone's linking mechanism (local NuGet package OR project reference) is deliberately undecided and MUST remain undecided until that decision is taken later — no part MAY resolve it.

6. **Minimum implementation.** Each part SHALL deliver the minimum that satisfies its directives. Caching, retries, added abstraction layers, config knobs, schema versioning, error-wrapping shims, backwards-compatibility shims, and migration code are OUT OF SCOPE unless a named directive in the owning part puts them in scope.

7. **Tier fidelity.** Every feature carried from 010 MUST keep its `[Core]`/`[Standard]` label. No part MAY retier, silently drop, or invent a feature absent from both 010 and the Berreman tree.

### Acceptance criteria owned by this slice

- AC-J10: After a sweep or fit is started, `JobRunner` MUST report progress as completed-points/iterations on a background worker, expose a single Start→Cancel toggle, cancel cooperatively within one inter-point/inter-iteration check, refresh results via MVU on completion, and write any derived artefacts only to the project sidecar directory (never the repo root).
- AC-J11: After the user opens a gallery entry, a shipped sample `OpticalConstructorProject` corresponding to an existing `Analytics/Examples/*.fsx` case MUST open through the schema-validated path, and the units glossary MUST state the §A.10 eV/cm⁻¹ conversions without re-implementing them; no `.fsx` is executed at runtime.
- AC-J12: After the user opens a multi-element system, the `SystemView3D` OpenTK viewport MUST render the placed `ConstructorElement`s to scale along the beam path and draw the reflected/transmitted beam segments read from the already-solved `EmFieldSystem.reflected`/`.transmitted` (`Fields.fs:553-554`), without re-solving the system, without re-deriving beam routing, and without storing any non-SI viewport coordinate back into the model.

