## Testing plan

Gates (always all three): `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `constructor-unit-tests` gate runs the new/extended `OpticalConstructor.Tests` files; must pass and increase the count over the prior slice's baseline.
- AC-J10 (`JobRunnerCancelTests.fs`): a started job reports increasing completed-points/iteration progress on a background worker; a `CancellationToken` observed between points stops the run within one inter-point check and leaves prior committed results intact; derived artefacts are written only under the project sidecar directory, never the repo root (headless).
- AC-J11: a gallery entry opens a shipped sample `OpticalConstructorProject` (corresponding to an `Analytics/Examples/*.fsx` case) through the schema-validated `openProject` path; the units glossary states the §A.10 eV/cm⁻¹ conversions without re-implementing them; no `.fsx` executes at runtime.
- AC-J12 (`SchematicGeometryTests.fs`, `SystemView3D` portion): for a multi-element system the viewport's element/beam-path geometry derives each segment direction from the already-solved `EmFieldSystem.reflected`/`.transmitted` (`Fields.fs:553-554`) without re-solving or re-deriving routing, and writes no non-SI viewport coordinate back to the model (geometry verified without an OpenTK surface).
- `build` gate green at Release/x64 with the public MIT FuncUI/OpenTK stack (clone unreferenced, linking unresolved); `unit-tests` gate (BerremanTests) stays green (not touched here).

## Risks

- **Medium.** Two correctness disciplines: (1) `JobRunner` cancellation must be cooperative via a `CancellationToken` checked between points/iterations and must leave prior committed results intact (no thread-kill, no retry loop, no scheduler abstraction), with sidecar writes confined to the project sidecar directory; (2) `SystemView3D` must CONSUME the already-solved `EmFieldSystem.reflected`/`.transmitted` directions and MUST NOT re-solve or re-route — the easy failure is re-invoking the solver in the renderer. Mitigation: prove the cancel-leaves-results-intact and the no-re-solve invariants headless; keep `SystemView3D` a pure read of the solved beam tree converting to viewport coords only at the render boundary; verify the OpenTK viewport is distinct from the §J.1 Avalonia `Canvas` and the §E.4/§H.8 Poincaré use. As the LAST slice, this closes the arc — confirm no clone reference exists in the UI fsproj before exit.

## Hand-off

This is the LAST slice of the arc: the Part J UX shell is complete. `JobRunner.fs` runs sweeps/fits on a background worker with cooperative cancellation, progress, timing, and the discharged operator-UX checklist (Start→Cancel toggle, MVU results refresh, sidecar-only artefacts); `Help.fs` ships the glossary/tooltips and the `Analytics/Examples/*.fsx`-sourced gallery opened through `openProject` (no `.fsx` executed); `SystemView3D.fs` delivers the reserved OpenTK system/beam viewport consuming the already-solved beam tree. AC-J10/AC-J11/AC-J12 tests green, and `SchematicGeometryTests.fs` now covers both AC-J1 (slice 014) and AC-J12. The clone remains unreferenced and its linking mechanism unresolved. Emit the final state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the final `constructor-unit-tests` count.
